{
  "stem": "13690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I said, you brought me so far.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I'm on the gates of the city now.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Why do you tell me to get off?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He says look, get off.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I said, I'm not going to get off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said, get off.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Back and forth, he's starting to say that I am starting to be very stubborn with him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He said look, there is curfew in the city that we are driving in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I have a permit to get back to the town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The town was on the German border.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The only way that you could do it is just get off the truck, and I will tell you what you should do.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I cannot take you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They will check the truck, they will find you, you are going to be shot and killed.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I noticed that the man speaks to the point and that he has a point, that I have no way.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I said, where should I go?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he said, look, I will tell you what you should do.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was seeing that he is quite reasonable.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, he said just go straight down that road, but when you reach the gates of the city, the houses which are practically deserted, the Jewish homes, just get into one of those houses that has the crossing and wait till you see the patrols.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There's a patrol in the city.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not of the Jews, they're just simply killed because it's curfew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's a patrol.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So if you will see the patrol, where they are going in, then you should run to the marketplace.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Otherwise, you won't be able to cross that place.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Sure enough, I was getting into that gate, one of those doors, and I was waiting till the patrol came.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
